</div></div></a></div><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Fusion, AGI, and interplanetary trave=
l are three of the most common themes in sci-fi from any era. All three app=
ear in Asimov&#8217;s </span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/e=
3526c21-0078-4fdc-8efe-7a662ef32a2d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNua=
MZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #404040; text-decorat=
ion: underline;">The Last Question</a><span>.</span></em><span> They&#8217;=
re humanity-altering technologies. In the past three months, during a perio=
d of doom and gloom and supposed stagnation, we&#8217;ve taken meaningful s=
teps closer to achieving all three. And the implications are going to be co=
nfusing as hell to work through.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">That&#8217;s whe=
re stories come in.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Those who understand today&#8217;s t=
echnology well enough to envision worlds born of its extrapolations should =
do so. Write sci-fi, make movies, create art, build monuments, bring back W=
orld&#8217;s Fairs.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>We should return to the days o=
f celebrating big achievements as they elicit feelings of pride in the publ=
ic towards doing impactful things. We should build </span><a href=3D"https:=
//substack.com/redirect/61e99287-cdec-49bd-ba4c-1fba92240fdc?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOX=
AwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"col=
or: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">more monuments</a><span>, new won=
ders of the world, and massive art installations. Statues of true heroes, s=
tructures like The Colosseum and the Taj Mahal, museums full of art ahead o=
f their time. Even amusement parks like Disney&#8217;s EPCOT (&#8220;&#8203=
;&#8203;Experimental Prototype Community of Tomorrow&#8221;).</span></p><p =
style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;">It&#8217;s not about blindly celebrating tech founders. It is possib=
le to be both optimistic and cautious.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040;=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">And, it&#8217;s n=
ot about being &#8220;nicer&#8221; to tech. Stories are simply a way to com=
press information and help people grok the positives and wrestle with the n=
egatives of everything going on. Negative stories have a natural advantage;=
 putting more effort into telling Good Stories would help balance the scale=
s. The impact of this cultural change would be immense.</p><p style=3D"colo=
r: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Humans=
 need narratives to make sense of things. Stories help us understand what t=
o do, what everyone else is doing, and how to do it. They ask, what is poss=
ible? What needs to be done? What Can You Do For Your Country? They are mot=
ivational, guiding, and inspiring. They are pure magic. They make the pursu=
it of the impossible attractive and attainable.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Th=
ere&#8217;s this great quote from Karen Armstrong in </span><em><a href=3D"=
https://substack.com/redirect/29a7d101-775f-4116-8784-80df30cd9659?j=3DeyJ1=
IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=
=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">The Great Transformation</=
a></em><span>: &#8220;Unless there is some kind of spiritual revolution tha=
t can keep abreast of our technological genius, it is unlikely that we will=
 save our planet. A purely rational education will not suffice.&#8221;</spa=
n></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;">I&#8217;d amend it in a couple of ways.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
">Unless there is some kind of narrative revolution that can keep abreast o=
f our technological genius, it is unlikely that we will reach our full, ama=
zing potential. A purely rational education will not suffice.</p><p style=
=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
">We need better sci-fi to guide builders who want to create a magnificent =
future, and dazzling spectacles to let people picture themselves in it.&#16=
0;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;">It&#8217;s time to tell Good Stories again.</p><div style=
